'''''Lost Dutchman's Gold''''' is a 1979 video game designed by Terry Kepner (as "Teri Li") and published by [[The Software Exchange]] for the [[TRS-80]] 16K.

==Contents==
''Lost Dutchman's Gold'' is a [[text adventure]] in which the player searches for gold hidden in the desert.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Jon Mishcon reviewed ''Lost Dutchman's Gold'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 34.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Mishcon |first=Jon |date=December 1980 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=34|pages=35}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "Overall, a good game of the adventure genre, well worth its reasonable price, but certainly not the best of its class."<ref name="SG"/>

